author: pburba
msg: On the inheritable-props branch: Fix some ordering and omission bugs with
proplist and propget when getting explicit props from the WC and iprops
from the repos.
* subversion/libsvn_client/prop_commands.c
(svn_client_propget5): Comment cleanup.  When contacting the repos for
iprops, don't reallocate the *PROPS output argument because we'll wipe
out the explicit props already obtained from the WC.
(get_remote_props,
get_local_props): New.
(svn_client_proplist4): Refactor into the two new functions above.  Get
the remote props first, to keep the ordering consistent.  Prior to this
change if a proplist got explicit props locally and iprops from the
server, then the local props were sent to the svn_proplist_receiver2_t
callback first and the iprops came later.  This was inconsistent with
the ordering of all propgets and proplists which obtained both explicit
and inherited props from the WC xor the repos.
